Introduced Version
HOUSE BILL No. 1172
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 10-11-2-33.
Synopsis: Rape kits. Requires the superintendent of the state police
department to: (1) obtain data from law enforcement agencies
concerning medical forensic examination kits in the agencies'
possession; and (2) report a summary of the data to the legislative
council.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Klinker
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Veterans Affairs and Public
Safety.
2026 IN 1172—LS 6225/DI 151

Introduced
